  "body": "NAK: this is a misunderstanding of POSIX.\n\nWrites to a file are immediately visible to other users of the filesystem, including metadata: `fsync` / `sync` are only needed to guarantee that the data is durable (on disk).\n\nFurther, `sync` flushes all dirty pages on the filesystem (including those belonging to other jobs) and this could be a real serious disruption on the worker node.\n", 
